def is_rice_cooked(rice:item):
    # Function to check if the rice is cooked
    symbol cooked=exists pot:item: is_pot(pot) and inside(rice, pot) and is_on(pot)
    return cooked

behavior cook_rice(pot:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(pot, stove)
        # Ensure the pot is placed on the stove
        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Turn on the stove

behavior stop_cooking(stove:item):
    body:
        achieve is_off(stove)
        # Turn off the stove

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind rice: item where:
            is_food_rice(rice)
        # Select rice to be cooked
        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot) and inside(rice, pot)
        # Select the pot with rice inside
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)
        # Select the stove
        cook_rice(pot, stove)
        # Start cooking the rice on the stove
        if is_rice_cooked(rice):
            stop_cooking(stove)
        # Stop cooking the rice once its confirmed cooked
